{"links": {"self": "/works/OL56800W/editions.json?limit=50", "work": "/works/OL56800W"}, "size": 34, "entries": [{"type": {"key": "/type/edition"}, "publish_date": "1988", "publish_country": "enk", "languages": [{"key": "/languages/eng"}], "title": "Silver wedding", "by_statement": "Maeve Binchy", "authors": [{"key": "/authors/OL21305A"}], "oclc_numbers": ["18757919"], "publishers": ["Century"], "publish_places": ["London"], "isbn_10": ["071262287X"], "pagination": "256 pages", "number_of_pages": 256, "source_records": ["marc:marc_columbia/Columbia-extract-20221130-002.mrc:247732367:769", "marc:harvard_bibliographic_metadata/ab.bib.01.20150123.full.mrc:490314400:456", "marc:harvard_bibliographic_metadata/20220215_016.bib.mrc:288688134:2190"], "full_title": "Silver wedding", "works": [{"key": "/works/OL56800W"}], "key": "/books/OL52822519M", "lc_classifications": ["PR6052.I7728 S5 1988"], "description": {"type": "/type/text", "value": "As occasion to celebrate, when Desmond and Deirdre Doyle must gather family and friends around them in remembrance of the twenty-five years of marriage they've shared. A moment of reckoning as an uneasy couple is forced to face a hapless daughter still struggling to become a nun... a son who prefers the bleak family farm in Ireland to London... the once best man, now Desmond's boss... Deirdre's bridesmaid, now a successful career woman... and their priest with his guilty secret. A time of transformation for their eldest daughter, Anna. For only Anna can confront their tarnished lives and find a truth to draw them into a circle of love that might nourish, protect, and finally heal them all."}, "latest_revision": 4, "revision": 4, "created": {"type": "/type/datetime", "value": "2024-07-23T12:53:38.766121"}, "last_modified": {"type": "/type/datetime", "value": "2025-10-30T16:35:22.281045"}}, {"type": {"key": "/type/edition"}, "authors": [{"key": "/authors/OL21305A"}], "local_id": ["urn:bwbsku:O9-BQT-489"], "publish_date": "1998-07-01", "p